Like square Otto bus @Provide annotation, it would be great if we can define Providers that will send a Telegram automatically when listeners registered for a msg :

``` java
MessageDispatcher.getInstance().addProviders(this, int ... msgs)
```

``` java
interface Provider {
   Telegraph provides(int msg);
}
```

When registering msgs, listeners will get Telegraph from providers registered for the given msgs.

When I have a Quaternion and try to get the angle:

``` java
Quaternion q = new Quaternion(new Vector3(1, 0, 0), 90);
float angle = q.getAngleAround(0, 1, 0);
```

Angle is NaN not 0 as it is supposed to be. This is due to the inaccuracy of the squareroot function of Math. This cases the value in Math.acos to be bigger than 1. I could solve it by casting the value in the Math.acos function (line: 850) to float:

``` java
return MathUtils.isZero(l2) ? 0f : (float)(2.0 * Math.acos((float) (this.w / Math.sqrt(l2))));
```

Maybe there is a nicer solution, but it at least solves the problem.

