It seems that #2322 (or something else commited since last snapshot) changed the behaviour of setting spacing end/or margin to an ImageTextButton.

``` java
ImageTextButtonStyle titleButtonStyle = new ImageTextButtonStyle();
titleButtonStyle.font = manager.get("title.font", BitmapFont.class);
titleButtonStyle.fontColor = Color.WHITE;
titleButtonStyle.up = new SpriteDrawable(...);
titleButtonStyle.down = new SpriteDrawable(...);
titleButtonStyle.imageUp = new SpriteDrawable(...);
ImageTextButton title = new ImageTextButton("Title", titleButtonStyle);
title.getImageCell().spaceRight(5);
title.getLabelCell().padRight(5);
title.padLeft(10);
title.addListener(new ClickListener() {
        public void clicked(InputEvent event, float x, float y) {
            // ...
        }
});
```

When I first click the button, the `title.padLeft(10);` disappear forever...

The `title` is added to a container like this :

``` java
Table table = new Table();
table.clear();
table.pad(0, 0, 0, 20);
table.add(title).left().expandX().expandY().fillY();
```

This was not happening yesterday with the previous 1.3.2 snapshot. Excepted behaviour is to have `spaceRight`, `padRight` and `padLeft` maintained.
